<hr size=1> Can a more seasoned EQer explain to me how as a lvl 39 pally I can begin to use my newly acquired MOTQ with 0 in piercing skill.  Can I fight weak greenies?  Or do I need to fight blue guys to get my skill up?  Anyone have any suggestions?  Thanks, Ell <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ussnaake.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ssnaake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/01 8:41:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> Unfortunatly you have to fight mobs that would give you EXP. If you are at 0points now in piercing i would suggest giong to trainer and put a few points in just to get it started. I didnt start my piercing skill until lvl 48 and now im 50 with a piercing skill of 193. <br>
<br>
Snaake<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/upigboyph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PigboyPH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/01 10:59:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> Put some skill points into it, and get into a group with some good friends and grind on some blue Mobs to get the skill up....<br>
<br>
Pigboy Phatheart<br>
39th Lvl Pally<br>
Officer of the Wardens<br>
Wielder of the Ghoulbane<br>
Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/utxporter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>txporter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 12:00:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> Hmmm...I would normally suggest getting a piercer for your offhand and raising it up like that.  But, I think that MoTQ is actually primary only (right?) and also Paladin only (never played, but I don't think they can dual wield for some reason. Am I wrong?).  But I am going to be in the same boat soon.  I am level 37 now and have my one and two handed slashing and piercing max'd, but both of my blunts are at 0.  I think that I am going to just ignore 2hd blunt and try to increase my 1hd blunt.  Is it a big mistake to ignore 2hd blunt?<br>
<br>
Beorc Lvl 37 Dorf warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/upigboyph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PigboyPH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 12:37:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> To answer some of your questions Beorc.....<br>
<br>
1.  Pally's do not get dual wield....so unfortunetely we can't stick one in our offhand....<br>
<br>
2.  MoQ is pally only and is 2 hand piercing so it has to go in primary...<br>
<br>
3.  The best advise I can offer you is:  as a warrior max out all your weapon skills.....you never know when you might run across a fatty weapon and guess what?!?!  I've only trained 1hs and its 2hs!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and there are certain weapons for certain situations also (different procs and such) so some people when grinding or what not get weight reducing bags and stuff what other weapons they might have into them so they have all their weapons at all times!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hope this helps some...<br>
<br>
Pigboy Phatheart <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stupie>stupie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 7:20:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> Another way to get your skill up you see a lot of ppl doing, just find a group fighting some blue mobs and ask them if you can practice on them, i have yet to see a group that has said no to such a request. Sure you'll get no xp or loot, but thats the price you pay i guess. I had the some problem when i got my first piercer, i had just 20 train points in it, i was able to build it up over two long nights of fear kiting cats in IC. Good luck either way.<br>
Stupie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vyper>Vyper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 8:47:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> Hehe, I had same problem with my 2HS.  60 skill points and a lot of dead Kodiaks later, skill up to 179.<br>
<br>
Vypr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/utxporter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>txporter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 11:11:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> Thanks all!  I will definitely work at it.  I am very behind in a lot of my skills. I was going to focus on Bash (somewhere in the 90s) and then 1hd Blunt (right around 0 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )!  I have been keeping my piercing, 1hd slash and 2hd slash max'd, so in about 2 lvls, they will be maxed until 50 anyhow.  I guess after I get 1hd blunt and bash up, I will start on 2hd blunt.<br>
<br>
Beorc 37 warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uvondegar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vondegar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/17/01 12:08:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> I was just recently in the same boat. I have used mainly 1hs, 2hs and piercing. Duelwielding 1hs and piercer. After hitting almost lvl 35. I saved enough money for a better weapon then the langseax and Walrus tooth combo. 11 29 1hs. This brought me to looking at higher damage weapons. After alot of thought. I found a Cane of the Tranquil. Problem though  1hb. Hmmm what to do. Other skills maxed at 175. 1hb at 0. I went to work. Buy a couple of High Dexterity armor or jewelery items. Executioners hood +9 dex, Grotesque mask +7 dex, Black pearl jewerlery can be Dex+6 per ring. Would be easy to raise your dex +20 or 30. with any buffs will help. Find a Low blue enemy. easy to kill. not much Hp loss. and just beat on them for a while. 1 after another. My understanding is the more damage you do the faster your skill will go up. Dex effects how often you will hit. I went this way and brought my 1hb from 0 to now 153 and just dinged 36. most of it in hell lvl 35. Good luck.<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amanar>Amanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/01 2:05:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> ya i know how ya feel...cept if your a ranger....its damn easy to get up! Find a blue animal... snare... fear... whack and fear for about 15 mins till he drops... i'd usually get 10 pts per kill about for my slashing at lvl 45.... hehe i know i used only 1hb till 45 as a ranger. But now at 50... well i wanted to train my hand to hand... but noooooo hand to hand for some reason lvls at about 1 per 15 min kill...  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uellassararathorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellassar Arathorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/23/01 4:23:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: piercing practice</span><hr size=1> anyone that would like to use MOTQ let me know, I'm not using it right now and someone else can use it and get good at it.  Send me a tell.  Ell <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=10.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepic